<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1357,2032]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1501,1527]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Distribution</emphasis>
. Northern Eurasia ranging from western and northern Europe to the Russian Far East (Kamchatka Kraj, Primorskij Kraj and Sakhalin) and 
<collectingCountry box="[606,746,1537,1564]" name="South Korea" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(Shinohara 1995).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1357,2032]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1573,1599]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Host plant</emphasis>
. Unknown, but probably 
<taxonomicName box="[606,731,1573,1600]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[606,679,1573,1599]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Betula</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.Gray" authorityYear="1822" box="[742,874,1573,1599]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
]. The Japanese subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1995" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicornis" subSpecies="ibukii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Pamphilius brevicornis ibukii</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1995
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[423,508,1609,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="156.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-26@156.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="156" captionText="FIGURE 67. Pamphilius brevicornis ibukii, male, Japan – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) genitalia dorsally, (h) genitalia ventrally, (i) claw." pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
), is associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[736,904,1609,1635]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ermanii">
<emphasis box="[736,904,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Betula ermanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[919,1068,1609,1635]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corylifolia">
<emphasis box="[919,1068,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. corylifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Shinohara &amp; Kojima 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Shinohara &amp; Kojima" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="platyphylla" variety="japonica">
<emphasis box="[1123,1281,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. platyphylla</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1338,1436,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">japonica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H." box="[159,462,1645,1671]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="145 - 152" refId="ref78403" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H. (2017) Host plant, larva and life history of Pamphilius brevicornis ibukii (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) in Honshu, Japan. Bulletin of the National Museum of Nature and Science, Tokyo, Series A, 43, 145 - 152." type="journal article" year="2017">Shinohara &amp; Kojima 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1357,2032]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1681,1707]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is a widely spread Palaearctic species with two subspecies recognized by Shinohara (1995). The nominotypical subspecies originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[743,829,1717,1743]" name="Finland" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Finland</collectingCountry>
occurs in the Russian Far East and 
<collectingCountry box="[1236,1308,1718,1744]" name="South Korea" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Korea</collectingCountry>
. The maximum intrasubspecific 
<emphasis box="[400,414,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">p</emphasis>
-distance within 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1995" box="[601,889,1753,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicornis" subSpecies="brevicornis">
<emphasis box="[601,889,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brevicornis brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1061,1753,1779]" name="Germany" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Germany</collectingCountry>
and Primorskij Kraj was 0.9% in COI (n=3) and the minimum distance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1995" box="[599,821,1789,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicornis" subSpecies="ibukii">
<emphasis box="[599,821,1789,1815]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brevicornis ibukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[887,951,1790,1816]" name="Japan" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Japan</collectingCountry>
is 1.9% in COI. This species (
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicornis" subSpecies="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brevicornis brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1995" box="[309,535,1825,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicornis" subSpecies="ibukii">
<emphasis box="[309,535,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brevicornis ibukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was retrieved as sister to (
<taxonomicName box="[848,962,1825,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[848,962,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName box="[993,1133,1825,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gyllenhali">
<emphasis box="[993,1133,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. gyllenhali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the COI tree with 99% UFBoot support (
<figureCitation box="[347,442,1861,1887]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–143" captionStartId="230.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,182,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-26@230.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 142–143. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius 142. histrio group. 143. inanitus group." pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 142</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1995" box="[504,728,1861,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevicornis" subSpecies="ibukii">
<emphasis box="[504,728,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brevicornis ibukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the sister of 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1034,1861,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[921,1034,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the NaK tree with 100% UFBoot support (
<figureCitation box="[250,348,1897,1924]" captionStart="FIGURES 156–157" captionStartId="242.[151,264,1660,1684]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,186,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-26@242.[151,1436,181,1636]" captionTargetPageId="242" captionText="FIGURES 156–157: Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius 156. histrio group. 157. inanitus group." pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 156</figureCitation>
). This result agrees with the cladistic analysis based on morphology by Shinohara (1995), though 
<taxonomicName authority="Middlekauff, 1964" authorityName="Middlekauff" authorityYear="1964" box="[151,519,1933,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatus">
<emphasis box="[151,295,1933,1959]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. infuscatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Middlekauff, W. W." box="[304,519,1933,1959]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref75014" refString="Middlekauff, W. W. (1964) The North American sawflies of the genus Pamphilius (Hymenoptera: Pamphiliidae). University of California, Publications in Entomology, 38, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="1964">Middlekauff, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Benes, 1974" authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1974" box="[532,777,1933,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borisi">
<emphasis box="[532,627,1933,1959]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. borisi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Benes, K." box="[637,777,1933,1959]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="298 - 314" refId="ref72854" refString="Benes, K. (1974) The Siberian species of Pamphilius Latr., related to P. histrio Latr. (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 71, 298 - 314." type="journal article" year="1974">Beneš, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Malaise, 1931" authorityName="Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[837,1142,1933,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis box="[837,969,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. virescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Malaise, R." box="[979,1142,1933,1959]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref74904" refString="Malaise, R. (1931) Entomologische Ergebnisse der schwedischen Kamtchatka Expedition 1920 - 1922. (35. Tenthredinidae). Arkiv for Zoologi, 23 (2 [A 8]), 1 - 68." type="journal article" year="1931">Malaise, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, were not included in the molecular analysis. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[373,582,1969,1995]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in his 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kontuniemi" authorityYear="1958" box="[870,1024,1969,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis box="[870,1024,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[1212,1312,1969,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis box="[1212,1312,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. For another member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kontuniemi" authorityYear="1958" box="[412,567,2005,2031]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis box="[412,567,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1995" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1995" box="[692,1012,2005,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maximus">
<emphasis box="[692,819,2006,2031]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. maximus</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1995
</taxonomicName>
, no molecular data were available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
